Legendary Comics proudly presents The Infinite Adventures of Jonas Quantum, an original sci-fi odyssey from two of the most exciting voices in superhero storytelling: Marc Guggenheim (writer/producer of the hit TV series Arrow) and visionary artist Freddie Williams II (Justice League America, The Flash, Robin).

Meet Jonas Quantum: a maverick hyper-genius with the power to cure death in the morning, time travel in the afternoon and unlock transdimensional wormholes at night. And what have you done with your day?

Blessed with the curse of infinite intelligence, there's only one thing Jonas Quantum can't do: play well with others. This thrilling action-adventure series spans cosmic voyages, history-changing inventions, and delusions of grandeur.

For the first issue, Quantum is starting with something simple: finding a cure for death. What could possibly go wrong, you ask? Well, as luck would have it... everything.

volume.name: The Infinite Adventures of Jonas Quantum

description: Darius Mistry and Amos Golem, Paranormal Investigators for Hire, are (reluctantly) called in by the police commissioner when his daughter has her soul stolen by a syndicate of soul smugglers. To recover her soul and stop the smuggling ring, Darius and Amos have to venture into an underworld of supernatural crime, children's television, and monster wrestling! The third issue of a 5-part series.

The Women of Marvel are taking over in September! That's right, Marvel's blockbuster female-led titles are returning to comic shops this month for ten new TRUE BELIEVERS titles. Specially priced at $1, these can't miss introductory issues provide the perfect window into some of Marvel's critically acclaimed female-led titles! From the high stakes espionage action of Black Widow to the out of this world adventure of Princess Leia. From the larger than life Ms. Marvel to the irresistible charm of Spider-Gwen - these fan-favorite premiere issues offer perfect entry points into the Marvel Universe. Hang on tight and see what you've been missing with these exciting TRUE BELIEVERS titles coming to comic shops in September!

description: Clarisse Norman is a shy girl who lives in the New Hampshire woods, training to become a psychoanalyst. During a trip to the northern forests, she kills her boyfriend for no apparent reason. After a trial finds her to be schizophrenic, she is sent to an asylum. Why is she obsessing with her own drawings? Why is shy studying an 18th-century alchemist, chased away from Europe for his deranged theories? And why is there a door that seems to give onto a sheer void, in the middle of the forest? Martin Mystère finds out that the veil dividing a rational mind from a crazed one is far thinner than you can imagine!
name: L'ALBERO FILOSOFICO

description: Martin Mystère and Inspector Travis investigate a series of cases of human spontaneous combustion that have affected some “Contacters”, namely people who maintain they can communicate with extraterrestrials. Travis fears that the next victim could be “Bill”, “The Prophet” of the Church of the Other World, a bizarre ufological sect. When Bill disappears under mysterious circumstances, the “Otherworlders” ask The Detective of the Impossible for help, but someone is secretly spying on their every move….
name: Minaccia dalle stelle

description: Martin and Java investigate the disappearance of Bill, the leader of a group of fanatic ufologists, and a series of mysterious deaths of other important “Contacters”. As he gets closer to the truth, the Detective of the Impossible finds himself face to face not with an extraterrestrial creature, but rather, a secret government project for remote control of human minds. The project, which has been in progress for many decades, is behind some of the high-profile crimes in American politics…
name: Fantasmi di Altri Mondi

description: What happened to the ten days that, in 1582, Pope Gregorio XIII “stole” from humanity? Why is the 29th February 2000 a day that occurs only every four centuries? Was there ever a 30th February? What terrible secret is hidden behind the series of ritual murders that are devastating London and whose victims are only people born on the 29th February? Martin Mystère provides an answer to these questions, and also busies himself with revealing many other mysteries regarding our calendar.
name: 29 Febbraio

description: During a fancy dress party where the defunct Professor Aldridge’s spirit is expected to manifest itself, Martin meets the beautiful Stella, while Diana makes acquaintance with the mysterious Surya. Both find themselves attracted and disturbed by these meetings, which cause embarrassment and tension between Diana and Martin. The morning after, Diana disappears mysteriously and Martin throws himself into the quest to find her.
name: D'improvviso una notte

description: Martin combs New York in his frenetic search for Diana and, little by little, he fits together the pieces of a plot hatched by a Satanic sect aiming to bring back to life the diabolic Mabus. It is a veritable fight against time to stop the irreparable from happening…
name: L'essenza del male

description: Amazon jungle, 1950s: a film troupe is mysteriously exterminated. Now, a collector of cinema memorabilia, A.J: Forrest, shows Martin what he believes to be the proof of the existence of the Amazons: the legendary horse-women that are supposed to have dwelt in the heart of the Amazonian forest. From that moment, Martin and Forrest are in the line of fire of a group of terrorists composed exclusively of women, who call themselves “Daughters of Freya”…
name: Il regno delle amazzoni
